cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the efficient computation of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) on mobile computing platforms, which falls under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), augmented reality (cs.AR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on optimizing CNN computation using OpenCL, which is a platform for heterogeneous computing across different hardware architectures, further supporting the likelihood of these categories.
